==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[Sybarita]], from Greek [[Συβαριτης]], from [[Συβαρις]] ‘Sybaris’ (an ancient Greek city in southeastern Italy noted for the luxurious, pleasure-seeking habits of many of its inhabitants).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'sɪbəɹʌɪt/

===Noun===
'''sybarite'''
# A native or inhabitant of Sybaris. 
# A person devoted to pleasure and luxury; a [[voluptuary]]. 
# a person addicted to luxury and pleasures of the senses


